{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9b4421ef-8cca-490e-bdef-0f99240fcaa6","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_z3xw2RY2ObrNT32sHzpcaS","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Reviewing project context"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_EGXbJztflGcgyTLtWi3z9Y","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-82092c012e6e442ab2bdd6d27a79739c/TestProject.csproj"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-82092c012e6e442ab2bdd6d27a79739c/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"65dc0106-b537-437a-809a-a1d4ef91d930","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nLet me look at the files in the current directory to see if there's relevant context, but this is likely a question I can answer from my knowledge about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nKey change: Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8 (or around that version), Microsoft introduced the \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" (MTP) as the default test runner. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, VSTest was still the default runner, but in MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the default changed to Microsoft.Testing.Platform only, and VSTest support was dropped or disabled by default.\n\n\nIn version 4.0 and later, the compatibility layer that allowed VSTest to work with MSTest was removed entirely—the SDK no longer generates a VSTest-compatible adapter, so `vstest.console` can't discover or run tests anymore. I should check the project file to give more targeted advice on how to resolve this.","outputTokens":414,"requestId":"BC2E:1C6615:22349A6:2619594:69FAAB72"},"id":"941da5b2-49ad-4980-9c03-97a70684bab5","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:46:21.056Z","parentId":"177cbedf-11ee-4201-883c-34fd85c10c30"}
