{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"81ef8bf7-c874-49a2-bffd-179f90b56f46","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest support by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0, the SDK exclusively uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)** as the test runner. The VSTest compatibility layer (adapters that `vstest.console` relies on for discovery) is no longer included.\n\n**Your options:**\n\n1. **Switch your CI to `dotnet test`** (recommended) — it works natively with MTP:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n2. **Re-enable VSTest compatibility** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsForVSTest>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsForVSTest>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is the intended path forward since `vstest.console` is being phased out in favor of the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"65dc0106-b537-437a-809a-a1d4ef91d930","outputTokens":221,"requestId":"BC2E:1C6615:2236FB9:261C0BB:69FAAB7D"},"id":"73512925-bb10-474e-b476-971f4aad4ed2","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:46:26.813Z","parentId":"481e6cc1-e111-467d-9208-aedc4eebd25b"}
